The gcc compilation is mandatory to go on with this step.

$ cd SYSTEM-TEST/trunk
$ make GEMINIX_ROOT=$(pwd) preparemultienv
$ cd ..

Copy the compile_ghs.sh script in this directory to SYSTEM-TEST directory
$ cp <path-in-your-pc>/PAIPL-FW/trunk/test/systemTest/compile_ghs.sh <path-in-your-pc>/SYSTEM-TEST
$ cd SYSTEM-TEST
$ chmod 777 compile_ghs.sh

Check/modify in compile_ghs.sh
- Variable gmx_root (GeminiX trunk)
- ghssharehost=<USER>@pcdata
- ghssharedestdir=/tmp/<USER>/GHS

If you want to keep compilation intermediate outputs in pcdata
$ export KEEPTMP=1

IMPORTANT: Verify that your pcdata user can do 'ssh' to the virtual machine which compiles
$ ssh <USER>@pcdata
[pcdata]$ ssh user@192.168.122.17
(Reply YES if this is the first ssh connection try,
YES is enaugh to exchange keys and you dont need to type user@192.168.122.17 password too)

Going back to your pc, execute from SYSTEM-TEST directory
$ bash compile_ghs.sh <args>


It is possible to follow compilation log in
pcdata@/tmp/<USER>/GHS/SYSTEM-TEST/gmx_demo/branches/developers/marta/socket_walkingBit_uipaipl/LOGGA_GHS

The executed script generates the DES binaries.
After compilation finishes (it can take more or less 10min), the ready-to-use binaries are in
SYSTEM-TEST/gmx_demo/branches/developers/marta/socket_walkingBit_uipaipl/bin 
